  "text": "Previous clinical trials of low-GDP PDFs showed no significant changes in Kt/V urea, as shown by urea clearance [CITATION_1] . The Euro-Balance Trial group revealed inconsistent results in changes in Kt/V in the group treated with Balance PDF [CITATION_2] . In our study, peritoneal Kt/V urea was significantly higher in the L-GDP PDF group at 4 months than in the C-PDF group. This difference was magnified among anuric patients and found to be present at 4 and 8 months. However, these effects of urea clearance were concealed at following visits. Contrary to urea clearance, creatinine clearance was not different between the two groups. This might imply that low-GDP PDF treatment could cause substantial enhancement of peritoneal UF along with removal of small molecules.",
